Some notes and tips for developing in ZOS COBOL DB2 CICS

John Braddock
March 2026


The ISPF DCLGEN screen (ISPF option D2 2).
This screen will generate a copybook member for a DB2 tablein an existing PDS suitable for copy into a COBOL program

Used only occasionally, this screenshot is a useful reminder of how to generate a copybook for a database table.

<screen image here>

Important points to note are
    a) the dataset member name which is limited to 8 characters
    b) change the action to REPLACE if the copybook already exists
    c) give the structure a name, otherwise DCLGEN just prefixes the 01 level with "DCL"
